      "notes": [
        {
          "category": "summary",
          "text": "The RADIUS protocol under RFC 2865 is susceptible to forgery attacks by a local attacker who can modify any valid response (access-accept, access-reject, or access-challenge) to any other response using a chosen-prefix collision attack against the MD5 response authenticator signature.",
